{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:35:01.523430428Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-ea5acac2","body":"finding_summary: In `src/cli/run.rs:2180-2188`, `interrupted_handoff_cleanup_candidate_with_dirs()` now treats `FileSystem::pid_record_matches_live_process()` returning `false` as proof that the interrupted owner is gone. That is not true for legacy pid files: `src/adapters/fs.rs:795-804` also returns `false` when `process_started_at()` cannot be obtained, and that lookup depends on `/proc/stat` on Linux or `ps` output parsing on BSD/macOS (`src/adapters/fs.rs:294-318`). In those environments a still-running legacy owner can be misclassified as dead and have its interrupted-state cleanup run early.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files: src/cli/run.rs, src/adapters/fs.rs\nremediation_hint: Keep waiting when the pid record is non-authoritative and start-time comparison is unavailable; only proceed once the process is definitively gone or PID reuse is positively detected.","dedup_key":"02c1a7996d82d7378d78a8e3932cd4eee06ae5e2543ecf0f80c4cc4f48580396","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414160444","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
